This paper discusses optimization techniques for improving description logic reasoners covering the Web Ontology Language (OWL). This topic falls under the area of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with reasoning and knowledge representation. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as binary SVM to learn proper heuristic order for applying rules in ToDo list. This brings in the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of optimization techniques to speed up reasoners, which falls under the sub-category of optimization (cs.DL). The paper also discusses the implementation of the FaCT++ OWL reasoner and its Java version JFact, which brings in the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with ontologies, which is a topic in databases (cs.DB).
